                  <persName id="t18290409-29-person356">
                  LEWIS 
                  RAPHAEL
               <interp inst="t18290409-29-person356" type="surname" value="RAPHAEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-29-person356" type="given" value="LEWIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-29-person356" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 21st of March I was at the Synagogue, and saw the prisoner going down the stairs with this coat under his arm; he went out - I went to him, and asked who he wanted; he made no answer: I walked after him, and asked what he had under his arm - he said a coat; I looked at it, and knew it to be my father's, who is <rs id="t18290409-29-viclabel176" type="occupation">beadle of the Synagogue</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290409-29-victim355 t18290409-29-viclabel176"></join> - I brought him back, and sent for my father down; the prisoner asked me to let him go - I told him I could not: he then said he took it from the vestry-room: he is not one of our people, and had no right to the coat.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290409-29-person357">
